      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/6/87. ¶  ¶ Tomorrow, noble Friend, the large box goes aboard the English mail steamer; so it will probably arrive at your place before the winter or rather in late summer. I will just hope that ver...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">87.06.26</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ferdinand von Krauss</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Stuttgart.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Krauss: 'Rep. 2. Nov. 87' [Replied 2 November 1887].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note>26/6/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Morgen, edler Freund, geht die grosse Kiste an Bord des engl.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Postdampfschiffs; so wird solche wohl vor dem Winter oder vielmehr im Spätsommer bei Ihnen eintreffen.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ich will nur hoffen, dass sich aus dem Inhalt recht viel Neues für Sie ergiebt.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Wie früher sind Watson &amp; Scull die Agenten.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Ch. French hat mir die Arachniden geliefert, Hr Dr Koch wird wohl noch nicht viele Arten vom östlichen tropischen Australien gesehen haben.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Gewiss wenden Sie ihm oder einem anderen Special-Kenner diese wichtige Spinnen Sammlung zu für baldige Bearbeitung.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es wird jetzt viel in den 4 Universitäts Museen Australiens nach<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">allen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Richtungen gearbeitet, so dass auch die Arachniden sicher bald<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hier</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>vorgenommen werden. Es wäre mir daher lieb, wenn eine neue Species Mr French gewidment würde. Es war mir besonders lieb, dass sich auch Herr Prof Hofman über die Colioptera gefreuet hat. So wird ihm auch wohl diesmal wieder aus der neuen Sendung Freude entspringe.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit den innigsten Wünschen für Ihr Wohlergehen</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Auch unter den Colioptere konnte vielleicht durch Hr Prof Hofman’s Güte eine Mr French’s Namen erhalten</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Mr French packt alle Insekten für mich.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Hoffentlich erholen Sie sich ganz in der schönen Sommerluft.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Bienen, Waspen u Ameisen sollen folgen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">26/6/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tomorrow, noble Friend, the large box goes aboard the English mail steamer; so it will probably arrive at your place before the winter or rather in late summer. I will just hope that very many new things will result for you from the contents. As previously Watson &amp; Scull are the agents.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Ch. French has provided the arachnids for me, Dr Koch<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Ludwig Koch</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will probably have not yet seen many species from east tropical Australia. Undoubtedly you will give this important spider collection to him or another specialist for rapid working up.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now much is worked in the four University museums of Australia in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>directions so that even the arachnids will certainly soon be worked on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">here</hi>
               </seg>. That is why I would<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be glad if a new species were dedicated to Mr French.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Charles French Snr.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I was particularly glad that Professor Hofman<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernst Hofmann.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was also pleased about the beetles.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to F. von Krauss, 3 April 1887<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 87-04-03b), M reported that a package of beetles was sent to Stuttgart.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The annotations on that letter show that the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>package was received on 16 May, and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that Krauss responded the same day, presumably including this information.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hofmann curated the Stuttgart collection from 1869, but the Australian Faunal Directory (accessed 28 March 2022) includes<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>four Coleoptera species with type specimens in Stuttgart, one described in 1898 and the others in the 21st century.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>So this time pleasure will probably also arise for him again from the new consignment.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With heartfelt wishes for your welfare</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Also one among the beetles could perhaps receive Mr French's name through Professor Hofman's kindness.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr French packed all the insects for me.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is to be hoped you will recover completely in the beautiful summer air.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bees, wasps and ants are to follow.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
